s IIa for England and Wales and Northern Ireland; it does not revoke it for Scotland, except for the provisions of Brussels IIa relating to the child abduction override—otherwise, Scotland is making its own provisions. The instrument revokes the maintenance regulation for all parts of the UK, except in relation to ongoing proceedings. Obviously, the Hague convention issue will apply across the UK. I hope that I have dealt with the points that have been made. If any remain, or if there are others, I am happy to write to Members. I therefore recommend that the provisions of the draft statutory instruments become law. Question put.     Share         Division 1  30 January 2019  The Committee divided:   Ayes: 9  Noes: 2  Ayes: 9  Noes: 2   Question accordingly agreed to.  View Details     Share       Share        Draft Civil Partnership and Marriage (Same Sex Couples) (Jurisdiction and Judgments) (Amendment etc.) (EU Exit) Regulations 2019            Motion made, and Question put,            That the Committee has considered the draft Civil Partnership and Marriage (Same Sex Couples) (Jurisdiction and Judgments) (Amendment etc.) (EU Exit) Regulations 2019.—( Lucy Frazer.)         Division 2  30 January 2019  The Committee divided:   Ayes: 9  Noes: 2  Ayes: 9  Noes: 2   Question accordingly agreed to.  View Details     Share       Share       2.59 pm          Committee rose.                     ×   Suggest Correction            Your Details:         Enter your suggested correction:   0 /1000          Please prove you are not a robot.        Close  Submit               A-Z index | Glossary | Contact us | Freedom of Information | Data Protection |  Jobs | Using this website |  Copyright     © Parliamentary Copyright                     Cookies: We use cookies to give you the best possible experience on our site. By continuing to use the site you
